b'Jonathan, Admin Assistant and ASL Student.
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\x9cWhen I got the call from Progressive, I was jumping around screaming!\xe2\x80\x9d Jonathan recalls the day he got hired and how excited he was to start in our House Counsel office in #NewJersey. Turns out, legal administration wasn\xe2\x80\x99t all he signed-up to learn. As Jonathan settled into his position, he found out that two of his coworkers were deaf. So right away, he started learning sign language in order to be a better teammate. Every day he picked up a few more signs. \xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99ve already learned so much more than I ever thought and it\xe2\x80\x99s only been sixteen months!\xe2\x80\x9d :clapping_hands::clapping_hands::clapping_hands: Jonathan says learning a whole new language has not only helped him personally, but professionally, \xe2\x80\x9cI know my coworkers appreciate it but it\xe2\x80\x99s truly been an invaluable learning experience for me, too.\xe2\x80\x9d

b'Eliani, Photo Estimator and Proud Citizen.
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
Born in the Dominican Republic, Eliani shifted between the U.S. and D.R. before settling in Cleveland. And when she started at Progressive two years ago, she felt right at home. In fact, when it came to acing her American citizenship exam, her co-workers were her greatest cheerleaders. \xe2\x80\x9cMy family at Progressive is so tight and supportive. I never expected it to be so good here.\xe2\x80\x9d Now, as part of Progressive\xe2\x80\x99s photo estimation group, Eliani helps customers decide whether their damaged vehicles should be repaired or replaced. She wants to be a role model for her son, Liam, by teaching him to strive for excellence. \xe2\x80\x9cProgressive sets the bar high and I\xe2\x80\x99m proud to be a part of that.\xe2\x80\x9d 

#PeopleofProgressive #PGREmployee #LifeatProgressive #RethinkProgressive #HispanicHeritageMonth #Claims #Immigrant #ThisisCLE'

b'Michael, IT Systems Analyst and Former Barista. 
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
Many Progressive employees might remember Michael from behind the coffee bar, because it was only a couple years ago that he was serving up lattes at the Campus 2 caf\xc3\xa9. Turns out, whipping up delicious drinks isn\xe2\x80\x99t the only skill Michael brings to the table. :slightly_smiling_face: In fact, he mentioned to a caf\xc3\xa9 customer one day that he was getting a degree in Information Technology. She said they were hiring summer interns and encouraged Michael to apply. He collected great advice from his customers on how to nail his S.T.A.R. interview and now, he\xe2\x80\x99s a full-time employee with Progressive. These days, Michael is building a whole new data center with project teams; validating applications and servers and meeting with subject matter experts from all different business areas. \xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99ve always loved talking to people. This time, it really paid off.\xe2\x80\x9d #PeopleofProgressive #PGREmployee #LifeatProgressive #RethinkProgressive #IT #Systems #Analyst'

b'What does an apron have to do with insurance? To us, that means protection. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we created the Apron Relief Program and committed over $1 Billion to assist our customers, employees, communities, and agents. Click link in bio to learn more.'

b'All active personal auto customers will be automatically credited 20% of their April and May premiums. There\xe2\x80\x99s nothing you need to do. We\xe2\x80\x99ll calculate your credit at the end of each month, and you\xe2\x80\x99ll see it reflected in your account within a few weeks. Once we\xe2\x80\x99ve calculated the credit for your policy, we\xe2\x80\x99ll automatically apply it to any outstanding balance or your next bill. And if you\xe2\x80\x99re already paid in full, we\xe2\x80\x99ll return the credit amount directly to your payment account or issue you a check. Click link in bio to learn more about what we\xe2\x80\x99re doing to help our customers.'
